  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Salesforce Developer (Ref 25720)",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities<br />• Design, build, and configure Salesforce applications to meet business process and application requirements.<br />• Develop and enhance system functionality through configurations and, where required, Apex or Visualforce customizations.<br />• Utilize Salesforce Omnistudio components (including Omniscripts, Integration Procedures, and DataRaptors) to deliver scalable solutions.<br />• Configure and support packaged or SaaS applications, manage releases, and maintain system stability.<br />• Conduct technical analysis and contribute to the design and configuration for system integrations and customizations.<br />• Collaborate with cross-functional teams to gather requirements, develop solutions, and implement enhancements.<br />• Perform thorough testing and quality assurance to ensure high reliability and performance.<br />• Provide technical guidance, training, and support to team members and stakeholders on Salesforce features and best practices.<br />• Stay current with industry trends, Salesforce updates, and best practices to continuously improve system performance and team effectiveness.<br /><br />Requirements<br />• Degree / Diploma in Software Engineering or related<br />• More than 4-5years of salesforce development experience </p><p>Technical Skills:</p><p>• Proficiency in Salesforce Omnistudio (Omniscripts, Integration Procedures, DataRaptors) is highly preferred.<br />• Experience with Salesforce Industries / Public Sector Solutions is a strong advantage.<br />• Knowledge in Packaged Development Estimating, Packaged Application Integration, and Software Platforms is beneficial.</p><p>Certifications: <br />Must hold at least one of the following (or an equivalent advanced-tier certification):<br />a. Salesforce Platform App Builder<br />b. Salesforce JavaScript Developer I<br />c. Salesforce Platform Developer I<br />d. Salesforce Platform Developer II</p><p><br />Licence no: 12C6060</p>",
